{
  "slug": "error-classification-thresholds",
  "type": "html",
  "title": "Procedural Error Threshold",
  "concept": "A system can tolerate small mistakes without changing the outcome, but when an error crosses a threshold where it likely altered the result, the entire process must restart—this balance between finality and fairness determines when flawed decisions stand and when they fall.",
  "interactiveId": "3ae41719-8aa4-416d-9b43-07c0154bbf45",
  "sourcePieceId": "41970d90-a746-4831-88ad-b712c8ae776b",
  "publishedAt": 1778724516885,
  "voiceScore": 94,
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Procedural Error Threshold</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --safe: #2d5f3f;\n    --warn: #c9a227;\n    --fail: #a23232;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 20px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--warn);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 3ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .decision-display {\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 2px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    text-align: center;\n    transition: border-color 200ms ease-out, background 200ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .decision-display.safe {\n    border-color: var(--safe);\n    background: #f0f7f3;\n  }\n  .decision-display.fail {\n    border-color: var(--fail);\n    background: #fdf2f2;\n  }\n  .decision-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    margin-bottom: 8px;\n  }\n  .decision-outcome {\n    font-size: 1.5rem;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    margin: 0;\n  }\n  .decision-outcome.safe { color: var(--safe); }\n  .decision-outcome.fail { color: var(--fail); }\n  .threshold-viz {\n    position: relative;\n    height: 60px;\n    margin: 20px 0;\n    background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--safe) 0%, var(--safe) 50%, var(--fail) 50%, var(--fail) 100%);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    overflow: hidden;\n  }\n  .threshold-line {\n    position: absolute;\n    left: 50%;\n    top: 0;\n    bottom: 0;\n    width: 2px;\n    background: var(--fg);\n  }\n  .threshold-label {\n    position: absolute;\n    left: 50%;\n    top: -20px;\n    transform: translateX(-50%);\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    white-space: nowrap;\n  }\n  .error-marker {\n    position: absolute;\n    top: 50%;\n    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);\n    width: 16px;\n    height: 16px;\n    background: var(--warn);\n    border: 2px solid var(--fg);\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    transition: left 200ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .reading {\n    margin: 18px 0 6px;\n    padding: 12px 16px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .reading strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .threshold-viz {\n      height: 80px;\n    }\n    .decision-outcome {\n      font-size: 1.25rem;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Drag to change the error's severity</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Small mistakes are absorbed. Big mistakes force a restart.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"error\">Error severity:</label>\n  <input id=\"error\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"15\" aria-describedby=\"error-out\">\n  <output id=\"error-out\" for=\"error\">15</output>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"threshold-viz\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  <span class=\"threshold-label\">Threshold: 50</span>\n  <div class=\"threshold-line\"></div>\n  <div class=\"error-marker\" id=\"marker\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"decision-display\" id=\"display\">\n  <div class=\"decision-label\">Decision stands or falls</div>\n  <p class=\"decision-outcome\" id=\"outcome\">Decision stands</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reading\">\n  Error magnitude: <strong id=\"magnitude\">15</strong>.\n  Threshold: <strong>50</strong>.\n  <span id=\"verdict\">The mistake is harmless—it didn't change the result.</span>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">The system tolerates small errors. The original decision stays.</p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var slider = document.getElementById('error');\n    var errorOut = document.getElementById('error-out');\n    var marker = document.getElementById('marker');\n    var display = document.getElementById('display');\n    var outcome = document.getElementById('outcome');\n    var magnitude = document.getElementById('magnitude');\n    var verdict = document.getElementById('verdict');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n\n    var THRESHOLD = 50;\n\n    function update() {\n      var err = +slider.value;\n      errorOut.textContent = err;\n      magnitude.textContent = err;\n\n      // Position the marker along the gradient (0 = left edge, 100 = right edge)\n      marker.style.left = err + '%';\n\n      var crossed = err >= THRESHOLD;\n\n      // Update display styling\n      display.className = 'decision-display ' + (crossed ? 'fail' : 'safe');\n      outcome.className = 'decision-outcome ' + (crossed ? 'fail' : 'safe');\n      outcome.textContent = crossed ? 'Decision reversed' : 'Decision stands';\n\n      // Update verdict text\n      if (err < 30) {\n        verdict.textContent = \"The mistake is harmless—it didn't change the result.\";\n        caption.textContent = 'The system tolerates small errors. The original decision stays.';\n      } else if (err < THRESHOLD) {\n        verdict.textContent = 'The error is noticeable, but still under the threshold.';\n        caption.textContent = 'The mistake is close to mattering, but finality wins. The decision stands.';\n      } else if (err < 70) {\n        verdict.textContent = 'The error crossed the threshold—it likely changed the outcome.';\n        caption.textContent = 'Fairness trumps finality. The flawed process cannot produce a binding result.';\n      } else {\n        verdict.textContent = 'The error crossed the threshold—it likely changed the outcome.';\n        caption.textContent = 'A severe mistake invalidates the entire process. The decision must be remade.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    slider.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
